29:33.336 --> 29:34.685
You killed her?

29:34.860 --> 29:36.862
l killed her.You killed her?

29:37.036 --> 29:38.341
Yeah.

29:38.515 --> 29:40.691
[TOBY GRUNTS]

29:42.302 --> 29:44.304
KROLAK: Say it.TOBY: I killed a little girl.

29:44.478 --> 29:46.697
Say itI... I killed a little girl.

29:46.872 --> 29:48.874
You killed that little girl?Yeah, I killed
that little girl.

29:49.048 --> 29:51.093
You killed that little girl?Yeah, yeah.

29:51.267 --> 29:52.965
Huh?Yeah, yeah, yeah.

29:53.139 --> 29:55.706
Say it. Just put your head
up to heaven and say it, Toby.

29:55.881 --> 29:57.970
What did you say? Say it!

29:58.144 --> 29:59.406
[GRUNTS]

29:59.580 --> 30:01.974
Say it, Toby![PANTS AND SOBS]

30:02.148 --> 30:04.106
Yeah, you killed her,
didn't you, Toby?

30:04.280 --> 30:05.934
KROLAK: Yeah, it's okay. TOBY:
I remember, I kill, I...

30:06.108 --> 30:09.546
Toby, Toby, it's okay.
l got you. l got you.

30:11.070 --> 30:12.985
l got you.[SOBBING]

30:13.159 --> 30:16.031
He practically blew him.[CHUCKLES]

30:16.205 --> 30:18.468
[PANTS AND SOBS]

30:22.951 --> 30:24.561
Coroner just called.

30:24.735 --> 30:27.129
They found chocolate
in the little girl's stomach.

30:27.303 --> 30:29.653
We got wrappers all over
the cab of the Indian's truck.

30:29.828 --> 30:32.700
KROLAK: Deputy![SIGHS]

30:32.874 --> 30:34.049
There you go.

30:35.094 --> 30:37.270
[TOBY GRUNTING]

30:37.444 --> 30:38.445
[STRUGGLING]

30:38.619 --> 30:40.186
Come on, Toby.Goddamn it!

30:42.231 --> 30:44.930
[PANTING]

30:45.104 --> 30:47.889
Come on, walk like
a policeman, Toby.
You're a policeman now.

30:48.063 --> 30:50.370
[TOBY GROANS]

30:51.458 --> 30:52.676
Okay to use this phone?

30:52.851 --> 30:54.940
SHERIFF: Yeah, go ahead.Christ!

30:56.680 --> 30:57.856
[COUGHS]

31:01.250 --> 31:04.775
You fish the lakes up here,
l'm told?Yeah.

31:04.950 --> 31:07.213
SHERIFF: Anglers haven't
been doing much.Watch your step.

31:07.387 --> 31:11.608
But spear houses have been
hitting pretty heavy.
It could be the snow cover.

31:11.782 --> 31:13.610
Could be that.

31:13.784 --> 31:17.136
What about the noise...[GUN FIRES]

31:17.310 --> 31:22.097
DEPUTY: He's got my gun!
He's got my gun![TOBY GRUNTS AND GROANS]

31:22.271 --> 31:24.099
KROLAK: Tell me when, Jerry.DEPUTY: Drop it! Drop it!

31:24.273 --> 31:26.014
[TOBY GRUNTS AND GROANS]

31:26.188 --> 31:27.755
COP 1: He's got Hamilton!DEPUTY: Let go!

31:27.929 --> 31:28.974
JERRY: Freeze!Put it down, Toby!

31:29.148 --> 31:30.497
[GRUNTS][SCREAMS]

31:30.671 --> 31:32.847
No![SCREAMS]

31:33.021 --> 31:36.285
Don't shoot me!
Please don't shoot me!
Don't shoot me!

31:36.459 --> 31:38.635
Toby, put it down!l kill little girl!

31:38.809 --> 31:40.333
JERRY: No goddamn it. No!

31:40.507 --> 31:41.464
[GUN FIRES]

31:43.162 --> 31:44.119
[GUN FALLS]

31:48.471 --> 31:50.473
Oh, God.
ls everyone okay?

31:50.647 --> 31:52.693
JERRY: Get a roll call!
Fitz!

31:52.867 --> 31:54.216
COP 2: l'm on it.

31:54.390 --> 31:56.479
JERRY: Fitz!SHERIFF: Hamilton! Michael!

31:57.263 --> 31:58.394
Are you hit?

32:00.092 --> 32:02.485
l don't think so.Oh, Jesus.

32:02.659 --> 32:05.227
All right.
Oh, Mike, you all right?

32:05.401 --> 32:06.359
[GROANING]

32:08.927 --> 32:10.580
Oh, my God.

32:13.148 --> 32:15.411
Jesus Christ.You all right?

32:15.585 --> 32:17.892
SHERIFF:
Get an ambulance. Do it.COP 1: Right.

32:18.066 --> 32:19.720
l thought he was
gonna kill me.

32:19.894 --> 32:21.940
You're all right.
You're okay.

32:28.729 --> 32:30.644
KROLAK:
What's that, the bullet?

32:32.080 --> 32:33.386
His tooth.

32:36.867 --> 32:39.914
[WOMAN ANNOUNCING OVER PA][AIRPLANE PASSING BY]

32:40.088 --> 32:43.396
Gate 42.
And they'll be boarding
in about a half an hour.

32:43.570 --> 32:46.573
ls that Concourse E?Yes, it is, sir.

32:46.747 --> 32:48.792
Thank you very much.You're welcome.

32:48.967 --> 32:50.751
Next in line, please.

32:52.971 --> 32:54.537
Hi, how are you folks today?

32:54.711 --> 32:57.627
Thank you.
Going to Cabo San Lucas today.

32:57.801 --> 33:00.369
Wadenah had been previously
convicted of similar crimes,

33:00.543 --> 33:02.806
a repeat offender,
still on parole.

33:02.981 --> 33:05.287
Regarding the alleged
suicide of the suspect
while in custody,

33:05.461 --> 33:08.682
state's attorney Paul
Ross has organized
an investigative committee

33:08.856 --> 33:11.728
to look into the tactics
of the Becker County
Sheriff's Office.

33:11.902 --> 33:13.817
Now we turn to John Qulgley
in Becker County. John?

33:15.254 --> 33:16.907
You okay?

33:17.082 --> 33:20.346
Hmm.
Yes, thank you.

33:20.520 --> 33:22.826
Sheriff's Department
investigators worked
in concert

33:23.001 --> 33:25.786
with Reno homicide detectives
for several hours,

33:25.960 --> 33:27.788
piecing together
the evidence trail

33:27.962 --> 33:31.487
that led to the brisk
apprehension of Wadenah.

33:31.661 --> 33:34.142
Authorities here,
while understandably disturbed

33:34.316 --> 33:36.840
by the brief hostage-taking
of one of their deputies,

33:37.015 --> 33:39.800
are taking some comfort

33:39.974 --> 33:42.716
in the swift justice
of this very dramatic evening.[AIRPLANE PASSING BY]

33:42.890 --> 33:45.632
[SLOT MACHINE WHIRRING
AND DINGS]

33:45.806 --> 33:49.723
[COINS CLATTERING][CLOCK TICKING]

33:49.897 --> 33:52.117
[SIRENS WAILING] Yet, while an investigation
is underway,

33:52.291 --> 33:54.641
the consensus seems clear.

33:54.815 --> 33:58.645
Wadenah confessed
after being identified by
the young snowmobiler.

33:58.819 --> 34:01.474
His suicide brought
a brutal end...

34:01.648 --> 34:07.045
WOMAN: [ON PA]
Final boarding call, Northwest
flight 1607 to Cabo San Lucas.

35:27.777 --> 35:29.170
[DOOR CHIMING]

35:30.563 --> 35:32.130
STORE CLERK:
Customer, Oliver!

35:39.049 --> 35:40.616
Morning.Morning.

35:40.790 --> 35:42.575
Nice day today.
Can we help you with anything?

35:42.749 --> 35:44.577
Anything in particular?

35:44.751 --> 35:46.448
Well, actually,
probably there is.

35:46.622 --> 35:52.062
l'm looking for a person.
Annalise, or Anna-Lisa Hansen.

35:52.237 --> 35:57.024
Yes. She would live above
the electric store.

35:57.198 --> 36:00.549
That would
be a small unit. lt's two
doors down to your left.

36:01.724 --> 36:03.857
Okay?

36:04.031 --> 36:07.774
And if l were you,
I'd go around the corner
and take the stairs up.

36:07.948 --> 36:09.906
You shouldn't have
any trouble finding her.

36:11.386 --> 36:13.127
And if you don't, come back.

36:13.301 --> 36:15.085
Thank you very much.
l appreciate your help.

36:15.260 --> 36:16.913
You're welcome.

36:19.046 --> 36:20.308
[CHIMES]

36:30.318 --> 36:33.713
ANNALISE: So, what is it
that you need to know?

36:33.887 --> 36:38.587
[SIGHS] Well, l'm trying to
fill in the gaps, uh...

36:40.285 --> 36:42.983
Fit all the pieces
together, Mrs. Hansen.

36:43.157 --> 36:46.465
[INHALES] lf you could
remember anything

36:46.639 --> 36:50.164
from when
you were interviewed, uh...

36:50.338 --> 36:52.906
Anything in particular
that might, um...

36:54.777 --> 36:57.127
It was Wednesday
and she never came.

36:57.302 --> 37:00.653
They said that she
never got on the bus,

37:00.827 --> 37:03.221
never even made it to
the school.

37:03.395 --> 37:06.224
Now, l assumed
that she'd gone home.

37:07.486 --> 37:08.443
[GRUNTS]

37:10.315 --> 37:11.925
[SIGHS]

37:12.099 --> 37:15.798
And, uh, wh...
What was she like, uh...

37:17.452 --> 37:20.629
What were your Wednesdays
with Ginny...

37:20.803 --> 37:22.849
What were they like?

37:23.023 --> 37:26.722
Oh, she would come in
with her little knapsack

37:26.896 --> 37:29.682
and plop it on the floor.

37:31.684 --> 37:33.860
Give me a kiss on my cheek.

37:34.034 --> 37:35.992
Big kiss,
always my left cheek.

37:39.387 --> 37:42.129
And then,
it was time for work.

37:44.697 --> 37:46.655
The moment she would sit
at the piano,

37:48.570 --> 37:50.180
we were all business.

37:52.226 --> 37:54.402
And l would give her

37:54.576 --> 37:59.102
her lesson just the same
as all my other pupils.

38:01.148 --> 38:03.846
And it was no "Grandma" this
or "Grandma" that.

38:10.026 --> 38:12.028
But the moment
we were done,

38:12.986 --> 38:14.335
she was my Ginny again.

38:17.730 --> 38:19.775
How could God be so greedy?

38:21.603 --> 38:23.126
Ma'am, l...

38:25.041 --> 38:26.347
[SIGHS]

38:27.696 --> 38:28.654
[CHUCKLES]

38:30.917 --> 38:32.397
And after the lesson?

38:34.486 --> 38:35.704
Cookies.

38:37.358 --> 38:41.971
We would have cookies,
if I'd baked them.

38:42.145 --> 38:45.105
Or sometimes l would
send her down to
the Land of Christmas.

38:45.279 --> 38:49.327
The store downstairs,
for candy or ice cream.

38:49.501 --> 38:53.069
She would eat her sweets
and l would read to her.

38:54.941 --> 38:56.595
She loved Andersen.

38:58.161 --> 38:59.989
Who?

39:00.163 --> 39:03.210
Do you know what he wrote
in his story The Angel?

39:04.603 --> 39:06.169
No. [CHUCKLES]

39:11.218 --> 39:12.306
Here.

39:17.442 --> 39:21.489
"Whenever a good child dies,

39:21.663 --> 39:23.622
"an angel of God

39:24.492 --> 39:27.626
"comes down from heaven

39:27.800 --> 39:31.499
"and takes
the child in his arms.

39:31.673 --> 39:34.720
"And spreads out
his great white wings.

39:35.808 --> 39:37.679
"And flies with her

39:39.159 --> 39:41.988
"over all the places

39:42.162 --> 39:44.643
"that she
loved during her life.

39:46.340 --> 39:48.603
"And then,
the child carries

39:52.346 --> 39:54.392
"a large handful
of flowers

39:56.089 --> 39:57.699
"up to God."

40:07.013 --> 40:08.144
Beautiful.

40:11.670 --> 40:13.672
[CHATTERING AND YELLING]

40:26.467 --> 40:28.643
JERRY: What's your name?

40:28.817 --> 40:30.471
Becky. Becky Fiske.

40:32.430 --> 40:34.388
And you were
Ginny's best friend?

40:35.868 --> 40:37.347
We sat together.

40:38.392 --> 40:39.654
She died.

40:40.742 --> 40:42.614
Yeah. l know.

40:45.138 --> 40:49.490
Her grandmother told me
that Ginny liked
to tell stories.

40:51.797 --> 40:53.102
Sometimes.

40:53.842 --> 40:54.800
[SNIFFS]

40:56.541 --> 40:58.325
What kind of stories?

40:59.674 --> 41:01.371
Ginny knew a giant.

41:03.373 --> 41:04.505
Giant?

41:05.550 --> 41:06.594
[CHUCKLES]

41:06.768 --> 41:09.075
Really?

41:09.249 --> 41:14.254
He was as big as a mountain
and gave her porcupines.

41:14.428 --> 41:16.648
She called him
"The Wizard."

41:18.214 --> 41:19.955
Ginny made a picture of him.

41:24.133 --> 41:26.048
Ginny drew
a picture of a giant?

41:27.659 --> 41:29.399
Can l see it?

41:29.574 --> 41:31.706
lt's on the wall in
the hallway.

41:31.880 --> 41:33.795
We put Ginny's picture.

41:35.928 --> 41:37.407
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

41:37.582 --> 41:38.931
l gotta go.

42:42.864 --> 42:44.518
[INHALES]

42:45.998 --> 42:47.477
[TURNS OFF FLASHLIGHT]

42:47.652 --> 42:50.002
[TYPEWRITER TYPING]

42:50.176 --> 42:52.178
Jean, hold my calls.

42:52.352 --> 42:53.962
[PHONE RINGING]

43:23.470 --> 43:26.081
I thought you were
supposed to be
fishing in Mexico.

43:26.255 --> 43:29.563
Yeah. [CLEARS THROAT]
I know, Stan.

43:32.087 --> 43:34.699
l went to the airport.

43:34.873 --> 43:36.439
l heard
the boarding announcement.

43:36.614 --> 43:40.618
And I... I just didn't
feel right.

43:42.402 --> 43:46.362
Something went off.
l need more time on this.

43:50.279 --> 43:52.586
You want me to reopen a case
because you got a hunch?

43:54.153 --> 43:56.242
[MOUTHING] Yeah.

43:56.416 --> 43:58.897
Jerry, no offense,
but you're retired.
You don't work here anymore.

44:01.639 --> 44:02.901
[SIGHS]

44:03.075 --> 44:04.119
Okay.

44:04.903 --> 44:06.948
l know, Stan.

44:07.122 --> 44:11.431
l know. But could you
run it through the
system for me anyway?

44:11.605 --> 44:13.346
You know,
just a standard query.

44:13.520 --> 44:16.479
Similar crimes,
profile, victims.

44:18.612 --> 44:19.918
Could you?

44:21.484 --> 44:22.921
Say, for...

44:29.754 --> 44:31.799
The last 10, 12 years.

44:33.105 --> 44:34.410
Could you, Stan?

44:42.680 --> 44:43.855
Please?

44:47.685 --> 44:49.687
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

45:40.041 --> 45:43.436
MAN: This is eight years ago
when this happened. [GROANS]

45:43.610 --> 45:45.699
I'm on the job only
six months at the point

45:45.873 --> 45:47.353
when this very big
deal goes down.

45:48.876 --> 45:50.399
Talk about baptism by fire.

45:51.836 --> 45:53.489
And to top off
everything else,

45:53.663 --> 45:55.100
it was in the
summer season.

45:55.274 --> 45:57.842
"Politics of tourism"
and all that nonsense.

45:58.016 --> 46:02.368
So we all feel the pressure
to make the bogeyman
of it all disappear.

46:02.542 --> 46:05.066
The brass were pretty
clear in the presumption

46:05.240 --> 46:07.460
that it was one
of those festival-goers.

46:07.634 --> 46:11.203
Which seemed like, you know,
a pretty good bet.

46:11.377 --> 46:14.075
Not to mention, a good
way to diffuse the kind
of panic that people get.

46:14.249 --> 46:17.557
You know, when they feel
like there's a bogeyman
amongst them.

46:17.731 --> 46:19.907
[GROANS] So we all figured,

46:20.081 --> 46:24.259
and l do feel accurately,
that's why we never
did catch him.

46:27.088 --> 46:30.439
The odds were
on a perpetrator

46:30.613 --> 46:33.834
who'd cleared the county
before the body
was ever found.

46:35.705 --> 46:37.229
Yeah.

46:37.403 --> 46:39.144
Look at that.

46:39.318 --> 46:41.799
Look at the slit
in that neck.

46:41.973 --> 46:44.062
I don't know,
but for me...

46:44.236 --> 46:48.936
For me, it's like
being in a movie.

46:49.110 --> 46:52.418
This stuff just doesn't
bother me like it does
some people. You?

46:55.029 --> 46:56.726
Luanne Rotze.

46:56.901 --> 46:59.251
A little 10-year-old girl.

46:59.425 --> 47:02.515
Real little. l mean,
real small for her age.

47:02.689 --> 47:04.647
You know what, though?

47:04.822 --> 47:07.433
As horrible as that
kind of thing is,

47:07.607 --> 47:10.436
l got an adrenaline rush
being part of it.

47:10.610 --> 47:13.743
I don't know if that's bad,
but, hey, don't hurt me.

47:13.918 --> 47:16.137
That's just the way it hit me.

47:16.311 --> 47:19.358
Nothing like it ever
happened before in that area.

47:19.532 --> 47:22.709
By the way, nothing like it
ever happened since.

47:22.883 --> 47:24.145
And l think that says a lot.

47:26.147 --> 47:27.888
You mind if l keep this one?

47:28.062 --> 47:29.672
I couldn't let you do that.

47:29.847 --> 47:31.457
We always like
to be of help, but

47:31.631 --> 47:34.242
strictly technically,
the case is still open.

47:35.722 --> 47:37.680
Well, then how
about the report?

47:40.466 --> 47:42.816
I'll make you a copy.
How's that?

47:42.990 --> 47:44.949
Sure would appreciate it.

47:45.123 --> 47:46.951
But keep it between us.

47:47.125 --> 47:50.432
I'm not sure what
the policy is on this
kind of thing. Okay?

47:51.607 --> 47:52.957
My lips are sealed.

47:54.872 --> 47:57.178
Lucy!

47:57.352 --> 48:00.181
A two-year-old horse is like
a woman. You can't
predict what they're gonna do.

48:00.355 --> 48:01.487
They're crazy.

48:09.364 --> 48:10.888
Excuse me. Sir?

48:11.453 --> 48:13.629
Sir?

48:13.803 --> 48:16.850
I wonder if you could tell
me where a man named
James Olstad might be?

48:17.024 --> 48:19.157
Olstad's not a patient here.

48:19.331 --> 48:22.856
Oh. Well, l believe
he's the custodian, sir.

48:23.030 --> 48:25.206
Maybe in the building,
mopping? But he's
not a patient here.

48:25.380 --> 48:27.469
Mopping in the building?Yeah, but not a patient here.

48:49.361 --> 48:50.318
Er...

48:52.059 --> 48:53.713
James Olstad?

48:53.887 --> 48:55.149
[BIRDS FLAPPING]

48:58.457 --> 48:59.675
Um...

48:59.849 --> 49:03.592
I'm Jerry Black.
I'm a police detective.

49:03.766 --> 49:07.596
I'd just like to talk to
you about your daughter.

49:10.469 --> 49:11.600
What daughter?

49:13.863 --> 49:17.432
You did have a daughter
that went missing three
years ago, didn't you?

49:19.739 --> 49:22.002
Did you come here
to tell me that, uh,

49:23.134 --> 49:24.439
something happened to her?

49:24.613 --> 49:25.658
No, sir. lt was...

49:25.832 --> 49:27.181
Did you find her
dead or something?

49:29.705 --> 49:31.969
No. No, sir. We're, uh...

49:33.231 --> 49:34.884
We're still trying
to find her.

49:39.411 --> 49:42.109
Anything you might
tell me about her?

49:42.283 --> 49:43.502
Could you describe her?

49:46.809 --> 49:48.028
Well, she...

49:48.898 --> 49:50.161
She must be...

49:54.992 --> 49:56.689
She must be different now.

50:02.825 --> 50:04.044
She was so pretty.

50:05.176 --> 50:06.133
Hmm.

50:12.748 --> 50:13.706
[SNIFFLES]

50:13.880 --> 50:15.751
I miss her so much!

50:15.925 --> 50:16.926
[SOBBING]

50:17.623 --> 50:18.624
Well...

50:21.931 --> 50:24.934
We just used to, like,
hold each other.

50:26.023 --> 50:28.373
[SOBBING]

50:28.547 --> 50:31.289
I was supposed
to take care of her.

50:31.463 --> 50:33.900
She was my little
girl, you know?

50:34.074 --> 50:35.032
[SNIFFLES]

50:35.206 --> 50:36.337
I just...

50:39.514 --> 50:40.776
Ah...

50:47.522 --> 50:48.958
Where is my little girl?

50:51.309 --> 50:52.266
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

50:53.137 --> 50:54.442
Where is my baby?

50:56.836 --> 50:58.403
The break is Monash County.

50:58.577 --> 51:00.622
Eight years ago,
we got a homicide.

51:00.796 --> 51:01.841
Same MO.

51:02.015 --> 51:03.756
Exact same victim profile

51:03.930 --> 51:06.889
description as the
Ginny Larsen case.

51:07.064 --> 51:10.110
I interviewed one
of the local officers
for the particulars.

51:10.284 --> 51:15.550
Little blonde girl,
10 years old, sexual
assault, throat slit.

51:15.724 --> 51:18.553
The photos show that
she was wearing a red dress.

51:20.642 --> 51:23.080
Detectives out at Morehead
covered this case.

51:23.254 --> 51:25.517
The case is still open.

51:25.691 --> 51:28.172
At the time of the murders,

51:28.346 --> 51:31.697
Toby Wadenah was in
Stillwater Penitentiary,

51:31.871 --> 51:34.352
doing time on his
own rape conviction.

51:34.526 --> 51:35.918
So, he couldn't have done it.

51:36.093 --> 51:38.138
Jerry, the man shot himself.

51:38.312 --> 51:40.488
What more do you want?You told him what he did
and he believed you.

51:40.662 --> 51:41.489
All right, let's just
calm down here a minute
and see what Jerry's got.

51:41.663 --> 51:42.751
You got something, Jerry?

